Prodorsum.
Without lamella or costula; bothridium standing away from the notogaster, directed anteriorly, formed by an invaginated cup-shaped structure; sensillus (
ss
) flagellate, smooth; rostral seta (
ro
) lateral on rostrum, lamellar seta (
le
) dorsolaterally, interlamellar setae (
in
) on tubercle, exobothridial seta (
ex
) anterior to anteriorlaterally of bothridium; in lateral view prodorsum with a furrow anterior of interlamellar region.

Ano-genital region.
Genital and anal apertures contiguous, pre-anal organ at the point where the genital and anal plates meet; seven or nine pairs of genital, one pair of aggenital (
ag
), two pairs of anal (
an
) and two pairs of adanal (
ad
) setae.
